WEBVTT

00:08.600 --> 00:11.620
Hi there, welcome to
this video where we

00:11.620 --> 00:13.240
are going to learn
about the attacker's

00:13.240 --> 00:15.680
perspective in
cybersecurity. Let's

00:15.680 --> 00:20.080
dive in. The goal of
the presentation is

00:20.080 --> 00:22.660
to emphasise the
existing risks posed

00:22.660 --> 00:25.500
by some unfriendly
actors, called

00:25.500 --> 00:28.700
attackers, in
cyberspace. In the

00:28.700 --> 00:31.240
video, firstly, we
will discuss what the

00:31.240 --> 00:34.780
attacker is. Then, we
will distinguish the

00:34.780 --> 00:37.000
common types of
attackers and examine

00:37.000 --> 00:39.240
their motivations for
engaging in malicious

00:39.240 --> 00:40.400
activity.

00:47.140 --> 00:48.820
According to the
dictionary, the

00:48.820 --> 00:51.160
adversary is someone
who opposes or

00:51.160 --> 00:54.220
resists. It is an
enemy or an opponent.

00:54.320 --> 00:57.680
A more specific term,
attacker, identifies

00:57.680 --> 01:00.380
someone who carries
out harmful actions.

01:00.520 --> 01:03.600
In the cybersecurity
field, an attacker is

01:03.600 --> 01:05.840
an individual or
entity that causes

01:05.840 --> 01:08.340
problems for regular
users and companies

01:08.340 --> 01:11.040
to perform tasks and
duties in the digital

01:11.040 --> 01:14.180
space. The attacker
can be a person,

01:14.180 --> 01:16.820
group or organisation
that conducts

01:16.820 --> 01:18.620
malicious activities
against digital

01:18.620 --> 01:21.980
resources. Typically,
we refer to such a

01:21.980 --> 01:23.760
person as an attacker
due to their

01:23.760 --> 01:27.660
aggressive or active
pose. Cybersecurity

01:27.660 --> 01:29.220
professionals
distinguish various

01:29.220 --> 01:31.320
types of attackers
and link them to

01:31.320 --> 01:34.920
specific motivations.
Today, we will learn

01:34.920 --> 01:36.820
about some of the
most common types you

01:36.820 --> 01:38.940
could meet or hear
about when doing your

01:38.940 --> 01:42.360
daily activities.
Insiders, hacktivists

01:42.360 --> 01:44.640
, script kiddies,
nation-state actors

01:44.640 --> 01:48.080
and cybercriminals.
Let us start with

01:48.080 --> 01:51.480
insiders. An insider
is someone who knows

01:51.480 --> 01:53.700
information available
within a group, due

01:53.700 --> 01:56.560
to being part of that
group. We are all

01:56.560 --> 01:59.360
insiders of various
groups. Typically, it

01:59.360 --> 02:01.780
is a regular thing.
However, in

02:01.780 --> 02:04.200
cybersecurity, the
concept of an insider

02:04.200 --> 02:06.700
threat refers to an
insider who not only

02:06.700 --> 02:09.340
possesses knowledge,
but also utilises it

02:09.340 --> 02:10.900
in a manner that
leads to negative

02:10.900 --> 02:13.240
consequences for the
group or specific

02:13.240 --> 02:16.460
individuals. For
example, let us

02:16.460 --> 02:18.540
assume that you share
your password for the

02:18.540 --> 02:21.500
gaming platform with
your best friend. The

02:21.500 --> 02:23.120
friend wants to
impress some older

02:23.120 --> 02:24.880
school children and
gives them your

02:24.880 --> 02:27.940
password. These older
children access your

02:27.940 --> 02:30.580
account and take
control of it. Your

02:30.580 --> 02:32.840
friend is an insider,
but the actions led

02:32.840 --> 02:34.500
to some negative
consequences from

02:34.500 --> 02:37.380
your perspective.
That is why we should

02:37.380 --> 02:40.080
all be careful when
sharing personal data

02:40.080 --> 02:42.640
. Another type of
attacker is

02:42.640 --> 02:44.460
hacktivists. The
concept of a

02:44.460 --> 02:46.380
hacktivist is
constructed from two

02:46.380 --> 02:50.360
words, hacker and
activist. A hacker is

02:50.360 --> 02:52.480
a person who knows a
lot about computers

02:52.480 --> 02:56.300
and computer systems.
This person utilises

02:56.300 --> 02:58.540
their knowledge and
skills to gain access

02:58.540 --> 03:01.040
to systems to steal
the data or disturb

03:01.040 --> 03:04.700
those systems. It is
a cyber hooligan. An

03:04.700 --> 03:07.180
activist is a person
who stands up for a

03:07.180 --> 03:10.520
cause they believe in
. A hacktivist uses

03:10.520 --> 03:12.940
their hacking skills
to send a message,

03:12.940 --> 03:14.320
usually about
something they

03:14.320 --> 03:17.600
perceive as unfair in
the world. For

03:17.600 --> 03:20.160
example, a hacktivist
who loves nature

03:20.160 --> 03:22.340
could disrupt the
website of a company

03:22.340 --> 03:24.340
that cuts down trees
in the forest and

03:24.340 --> 03:28.180
sells timber. Script
kiddies make another

03:28.180 --> 03:31.320
type of adversary
actor. Script kiddies

03:31.320 --> 03:33.360
possess some skills
and knowledge that

03:33.360 --> 03:35.480
enable them to break
into or disturb

03:35.480 --> 03:38.640
computer systems.
However, they lack

03:38.640 --> 03:40.340
the necessary
knowledge and skills

03:40.340 --> 03:42.600
to comprehend the
implications of their

03:42.600 --> 03:45.720
actions. Typically,
script kiddies are

03:45.720 --> 03:47.800
eager to discover
software and run or

03:47.800 --> 03:51.280
test it, sometimes to
show off. For example

03:51.280 --> 03:53.060
, your friend could
use specialized

03:53.060 --> 03:55.000
software to run at
school and

03:55.000 --> 03:57.020
potentially disrupt
the entire school

03:57.020 --> 03:59.740
network by specifying
program parameters

03:59.740 --> 04:03.280
during execution. If
your friend has no

04:03.280 --> 04:05.780
idea how everything
is developed and why

04:05.780 --> 04:08.460
the software behaves
in a certain way, it

04:08.460 --> 04:10.460
means we have some
script kiddies around

04:10.460 --> 04:15.300
. Cybercriminals are
adversary actors or

04:15.300 --> 04:17.560
attackers with larger
goals than just

04:17.560 --> 04:19.120
disrupting the
school's computer

04:19.120 --> 04:21.560
network or public
services.

04:22.040 --> 04:24.340
Cybercriminals are
highly ambitious and

04:24.340 --> 04:28.160
seek financial or
reputational gain. Do

04:28.160 --> 04:29.560
you have a
supermarket around

04:29.560 --> 04:32.200
where you go from
time to time? The

04:32.200 --> 04:33.920
targets of
cybercriminals could

04:33.920 --> 04:35.840
target payment
systems, cash

04:35.840 --> 04:38.260
registers, and some
specialized logistics

04:38.260 --> 04:40.900
systems.
Cybercriminals could

04:40.900 --> 04:42.740
attempt to steal data
about the credit

04:42.740 --> 04:47.180
cards used in these
systems. In the news,

04:47.180 --> 04:49.020
you might have heard
about state-sponsored

04:49.020 --> 04:52.020
actors. It is not a
secret that among

04:52.020 --> 04:54.240
more than 200
countries globally,

04:54.240 --> 04:56.960
there are alliances
and opposing parties.

04:57.720 --> 04:59.700
Among the alliances,
there are

04:59.700 --> 05:01.540
competitions in
innovations and

05:01.540 --> 05:04.780
disagreements over
values. Thus, states

05:04.780 --> 05:07.000
sponsor some hacker
groups to sabotage

05:07.000 --> 05:09.840
events or to engage
in espionage, aiming

05:09.840 --> 05:11.900
to get data or
specific knowledge

05:11.900 --> 05:16.780
related to secret
information. Now you

05:16.780 --> 05:19.120
know several types of
adversaries and their

05:19.120 --> 05:22.100
motivation to perform
adversarial actions.

05:22.100 --> 05:24.240
Could you think of
one sentence to

05:24.240 --> 05:26.320
describe each of the
adversary actors

05:26.320 --> 05:29.600
listed in the slide?
Let us take half a

05:29.600 --> 05:30.780
minute to think.

05:59.100 --> 06:01.560
Was it enough time to
find the proper words

06:01.560 --> 06:03.420
in trying to
distinguish all types

06:03.420 --> 06:07.080
? One more thing to
mention. When your

06:07.080 --> 06:09.120
computer freezes or
your phone stops

06:09.120 --> 06:11.240
working, it does not
mean that you have

06:11.240 --> 06:13.860
been attacked. To
attribute the

06:13.860 --> 06:15.840
incident to a
particular adversary,

06:15.840 --> 06:17.500
an investigation is
needed.

06:19.460 --> 06:21.380
Thank you for
watching!